.TH MKDIR 1 "November 2024" "Userland Utilities" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mkdir \- make directories
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mkdir
.RI [ \-p ]
.RI [ \-m
.IR mode ]
.IR directory ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Create directories with specified names.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-p
Create parent directories as needed. No error if existing.
.TP
.BI \-m " mode"
Set permission mode (as in chmod), default is a=rwx minus umask bits.
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose mode (print created directories).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B >0
Error occurred.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B mkdir newdir
Create directory 'newdir'.
.TP
.B mkdir \-p parent/child/grandchild
Create nested directories.
.TP
.B mkdir \-m 755 newdir
Create directory with specific permissions.
.SH STANDARDS
POSIX.1-2017
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rmdir (1),
.BR chmod (1)
